padmavati was an ancient city mentioned in several classic sanskrit texts, malatimadhavam of bhavabhuti], harshacharita of bana, and sarasvatīkaṇṭhabharaṇa of raja bhoja. bhavabhuti describes the city with tall mansions and temples with shikharas and gates, located between para and the sindhu rivers. it is also mentioned in inscriptions like the kokkala grahapati inscription of khajuraho. the inscription mentions that the city had rows of tall mansions. the dust used to arise because of running of strong horses.